# Vercel Speed Insights Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Nidham HR Next.js project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` version 2.0.0 via npm
- Updated `package.json` to include the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with the resolved dependency tree

### 2. Configuration
**File Modified:** `src/app/layout.tsx`

**Changes:**
- Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component at the end of the body section (just before the closing `</body>` tag)

**Location:** The component was placed after all other app content, following the official Vercel documentation recommendation for Next.js App Router projects.

## Implementation Details

### Approach
1. Fetched the latest official Vercel Speed Insights documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart
2. Identified the project as a Next.js App Router application (based on the presence of `src/app/layout.tsx`)
3. Used npm as the package manager (confirmed by the presence of `package-lock.json`)
4. Followed the framework-specific instructions for Next.js App Router

### Why These Choices
- **Component Placement:** Placed at the end of the body section to ensure it doesn't block the initial page render, following Vercel's best practices
- **Import Path:** Used `@vercel/speed-insights/next` which is the framework-specific import optimized for Next.js
- **No Additional Configuration:** The component works out of the box with zero-config when deployed to Vercel

